Classes
Class
Description
Background
Background class for rendering backgrounds efficiently within the game
Block
Block class - one of the tiles in the game
changePassword
changePassword class to create a frame where the user can change their current password
Collision
Collision method to check if the player is currently making contact to a block
Game
Game class contains a frame that projects a game panel.
GameManager
GameManager class to manage different screens within the game.
GamePanel
GamePanel class to keep track of the actual game
GameState
GameState is an abstract class that the other game states of the game can use
Images
Images class for rendering images for our game
Leaderboard
Leaderboard class to create a window that displays the leaderboard of top ten scores
Level1State
Level1State class is a GameState class for the first level of the game.
Level2State
Level2State class is a GameState class for the second level of the game.
Level3State
Level3State class is a GameState class for the third level of the game.
MainMenu
MainMenu class to display a window for the main menu
Map
Map class for loading maps and retrieving data.
MenuState
MenuState class for the state of the game while it is in the menu
MovingBlock
MovingBlock class, a tile that can move from one x bound to another.
Player
Player class for movement around the game, as well as displaying score and a background.
PlayerType
PlayerType class to represent the player's account within the game, storing their username and their password
Start
Start method to open new frame for users to register or sign in
TitleScreen
TitleScreen.java is a class that creates a window for a title screen before the main menu.
TutorialPage
TutorialPage class to create the window for the How To Play section of our game
